    <string name="help_title_configurations">Help: Configurations</string>
    <string name="help_configurations"><![CDATA[Tap on the add icon (<img src="add_icon"/>) to create
                        a new configuration. A configuration defines the TRS-80 model and the disk
                        images used for the emulation. Tap on a configuration to run the emulator.
                        Use the info button <img src="info_icon"/> to show more details.
                        Long-press to re-order configurations.
                        Note that currently only Model I and Model III emulation is supported.]]></string>
    <string name="help_title_edit_configuration">Help: Edit Configuration</string>
    <string name="help_edit_configuration"><![CDATA[A configuration defines the parameters used by the
                        emulator. Select the TRS-80 model to emulate.
                        Note that currently only Model I and Model III emulation is supported.
                        If no disk images are defined,
                        the TRS-80 ROM will launch the BASIC interpreter. Disk images need to be
                        copied to the SD card. This app does not contain disk images for copyright
                        reasons. You can search the Internet for
                        \'<a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=trs-80+disk+images">TRS-80 disk
                        images</a>\'.<p>
                        A default blank cassette tape is created for each new configuration.
                        A different file can be mounted as the cassette image file.
                        Different keyboard types can be configured for portrait and landscape
                        orientation. The original keyboard mimics the layout of the TRS-80
                        keyboard. The compact layout is appropriate for smaller screen sizes.
                        The gaming layout offers a joystick control.
                        The tilt interface uses the accelerometer to control the cursor keys.
                        Touching the screen anywhere triggers the SPACE key.]]></string>
    <string name="help_title_settings">Help: Settings</string>
    <string name="help_settings"><![CDATA[The emulator requires the original ROM images of the
                        various TRS-80 models. ROM images for the TRS-80 need to be copied
                        to the SD card before running the emulator.
                        For copyright reasons this app does not bundle ROM images. However, the setup
                        assistant helps with downloading and installing ROM images from
                        the Internet.]]></string>
    <string name="help_title_emulator">Help: Emulator</string>
    <string name="help_emulator"><![CDATA[Pausing the emulator will store its current state. The
                        TRS-BASIC CLOAD/CSAVE commands will read and write to the cassette. The cassette
                        needs to be rewound before using the CLOAD command. Different
                        keyboard types for portrait and landscape mode as well as different disk and cassette
                        images can be mounted while emulator is paused from
                        the main configurations list view. Attach an external physical keyboard for better
                        usability.<p>
                        The following menu options are available in portrait mode:<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="pause_icon"/>: Pause emulator<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="reset_icon"/>: Reset emulator<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="rewind_icon"/>: Rewind cassette<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="sound_on_icon"/>: Mute sound<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="keyboard_icon"/>: Switch keyboard type<p>
                        Start the tutorial to run some TRS-commands.]]></string>

